{"body": "@drogus I see you've committed it now. It seems fine, although reading the code I think that `new_target` and `target` are not the same. `new_target` gets merged into the existing target. Example:\n\n``` ruby\npost.comments = [c1, c2]\npost.comments.replace([c3, c1]) # => [c3, c1]\npost.comments # => [c1, c3]\n```\n\nWhether this matters is debatable. I'm not really bothered.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/5790231", "created_at": "2012-05-18T16:39:14Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/6237#issuecomment-5790231", "updated_at": "2012-05-18T16:39:14Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 6237, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jonleighton", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F798cebccb32617ad94123450fd137104.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/received_events", "gravatar_id": "2940bc7d4506f3e099e3dcc32a412b98", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jonleighton", "type": "User", "id": 1979, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jonleighton/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52380c50bd3543c15100d12f"}, "id": 5790231, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/6237"}
